
Overview of noun accompaniment

The noun accompaniment has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                  
1. (1) accompaniment, concomitant, attendant, co-occurrence -- (an event or situation that happens at the same time as or in connection with another)
2. (1) accompaniment, musical accompaniment, backup, support -- (a musical part (vocal or instrumental) that supports or provides background for other musical parts)
3. complement, accompaniment -- (something added to complete or embellish or make perfect; "a fine wine is a perfect complement to the dinner"; "wild rice was served as an accompaniment to the main dish")
4. escort, accompaniment -- (the act of accompanying someone or something in order to protect them)
